    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-07T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="524"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/8–746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to the
                        British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Attlee</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="33" xml:id="d524fn33">Sent to London as Department’s
                        telegram 5877. The message was repeated to the Secretary of State in
                        telegram 3955 (<gloss target="#t_Secdel1">Secdel</gloss> 631), August 8, 6
                        p.m., to Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-07T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 7, 1946—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal for Prime Minister Attlee from President Truman. I regret that I was not
                    able promptly to give you a definite reply to your telegram of July 25 asking
                    for my views with regard to the recommendations of the American and British
                    groups concerning Palestine. Mr. Byrnes and Mr. Harriman have, I believe,
                    discussed the matter with you and have explained that I do not feel myself able
                    in present circumstances to accept the plan proposed as a joint Anglo-American
                    plan.</p>
                <p>The whole matter is being carefully reviewed in Washington and I hope in the not
                    too distant future to give you a more definite reply as to our position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
